## Edit Class for Mouse Embryo
## Class to prepare mini atlas as training batch
class Mouse_Dataset(Dataset):
    def __init__(self, features, labels):
        super(Root_Dataset).__init__()
        self.features = features
        self.labels = labels
        self.celltype = np.array([i.split('_', 1)[0] for i in self.labels], dtype='int')
        self.timebin = np.array([i.split('_', 1)[1] for i in self.labels], dtype='float32')
    def __len__(self):
        return len(self.features)
    def __getitem__(self, idx):
        ## idx for number of cell types
        idx = int(np.random.choice(range(24),1))
        cell_list = []
        if idx in [0,1,2,4,7,9,10,11,23]:
            ## k for number of time bins
            ## Complete celltypes : celltypes that have reasonable representation in each time bin
            for k in range(0,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [3]:
            ## No precursor, set to 'zero'
            for k in range(0,2):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==0) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                # Set all values to zeros
                sample[:] = 0
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(2,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [8,22]:
            ## No precursor, set to 'zero'
            for k in range(0,1):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==0) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                # Set all values to zeros
                sample[:] = 0
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(1,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [5]:
            ## 'neuralectoderm as precursors'
            for k in range(0,3):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==2) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(3,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [13, 18]:
            ## 'neuralectoderm as precursors'
            for k in range(0,3):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==2) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(3,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [21]:
            ## 'neuralectoderm as precursors'
            for k in range(0,5):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==2) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(5,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [6]:
            ## 'mesoderm as precursors'
            for k in range(0,1):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==0) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(1,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [12]:
            ## 'mesoderm as precursors'
            for k in range(0,6):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==0) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(6,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [14]:
            ## 'epithelial as precursors'
            for k in range(0,3):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==4) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(3,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [15]:
            ## 'sample previous and later cells equally'
            for k in [2]:
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==int(np.random.choice([1,3],1))))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in [0,1,3,4,5,6,7,8,9,10]:
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [17]:
            ## 'sample previous and later cells equally'
            for k in [6]:
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==int(np.random.choice([5,7],1))))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in [0,1,2,3,4,5,7,8,9,10]:
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [16,19]:
            ## 'zero and white blood cells'
            for k in range(0,1):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==0) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                # Set all values to zeros
                sample[:] = 0
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in [1,2,3,4,5]:
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==8) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(6,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        elif idx in [20]:
            ## 'zero and white blood cells'
            for k in range(0,1):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==0) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                # Set all values to zeros
                sample[:] = 0
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in [1,2,3]:
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==8) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
            for k in range(4,11):
                sample = np.copy(self.features[np.random.choice(np.where((self.celltype==idx) & (self.timebin==k))[0], 1), :]).astype(np.float32).reshape(-1)
                cell_list.append(sample)
        cell_seq = {}
        cell_seq['x']=np.array(cell_list)
        cell_seq['y']=idx
        return cell_seq

with open("./Data/genesys_mouse_embryo_11_clusters_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_data.pkl", 'rb') as file_handle:
    data = pickle.load(file_handle)
    
batch_size = 512
dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_test'], data['y_test'])
loader = DataLoader(dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
train_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_train'], data['y_train'])
train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
val_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_val'], data['y_val'])
val_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)

In [10]:
input_size = data['X_train'].shape[1]
## 24 cell types
output_size = 24
time_bins = 11
embedding_dim = 256
hidden_dim = 256
n_layers = 2
clip = 5
path = "./"
device = "cuda"
n_epochs = 100
train_on_gpu=True
In [11]:
model = ClassifierLSTM(input_size, output_size, embedding_dim, hidden_dim, n_layers).to(device)
optimizer = optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=1e-3)
sch = optim.lr_scheduler.ReduceLROnPlateau(optimizer, factor=0.5, patience=10, threshold=0.05, verbose=True)
In [12]:
logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
best_val_acc = 0
best_loss = 10000
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            ## time bins
            #t = np.random.choice(time_bins)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= best_val_acc) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)

dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_test'], data['y_test'])
loader = DataLoader(dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,

                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)

                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)

In [16]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)
#if cmat:
    # Plot validation confusion matrix
#    self.plot_cfmt(self.val_stats['pred'], self.val_stats['true'], 0.05, 'val_cfmt.pdf')

                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)

In [27]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue2.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue2.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)
#if cmat:

#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue3.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue3.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)
#if cmat:
    # Plot validation confusion matrix
#    self.plot_cfmt(self.val_stats['pred'], self.val_stats['true'], 0.05, 'val_cfmt.pdf')

In [49]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue4.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue4.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)
#if cmat:
    # Plot validation confusion matrix
#    self.plot_cfmt(self.val_stats['pred'], self.val_stats['true'], 0.05, 'val_cfmt.pdf')

                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)

sch = optim.lr_scheduler.ReduceLROnPlateau(optimizer, factor=0.5, patience=10, threshold=0.05, verbose=True)

In [60]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue5.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue5.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)
#if cmat:
    # Plot validation confusion matrix
#    self.plot_cfmt(self.val_stats['pred'], self.val_stats['true'], 0.05, 'val_cfmt.pdf')

In [63]:
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()

color = 'tab:red'
ax1.set_xlabel('Epoch')
ax1.set_ylabel('Total Loss (classifier + TD-VAE)', color=color)
ax1.plot(log.index, log['tloss'], color=color)
ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color)

ax2 = ax1.twinx()  # instantiate a second axes that shares the same x-axis

color = 'tab:blue'
ax2.set_ylabel('Validation Accuracy (classifier)', color=color)  # we already handled the x-label with ax1
ax2.plot(log.index, log['val_acc'], color=color)
ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color)

fig.tight_layout()  # otherwise the right y-label is slightly clipped
plt.show()

with open("./Data/genesys_mouse_embryo_11_clusters_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_data.pkl", 'rb') as file_handle:
    data = pickle.load(file_handle)
    
batch_size = 512
dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_test'], data['y_test'])
loader = DataLoader(dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
train_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_train'], data['y_train'])
train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
val_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_val'], data['y_val'])
val_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)

In [ ]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue6.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue6.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)

In [93]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue7.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue7.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)
#if cmat:

batch_size = 512
dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_test'], data['y_test'])
loader = DataLoader(dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
train_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_train'], data['y_train'])
train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
val_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_val'], data['y_val'])
val_loader = DataLoader(val_dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)

## 24 cell types

time_bins = 11
embedding_dim = 256
hidden_dim = 256
n_layers = 2
clip = 5
path = "./"
device = "cuda"
n_epochs = 100
train_on_gpu=True
In [100]:
model = ClassifierLSTM(input_size, output_size, embedding_dim, hidden_dim, n_layers).to(device)
optimizer = optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=1e-3)
sch = optim.lr_scheduler.ReduceLROnPlateau(optimizer, factor=0.5, patience=10, threshold=0.05, verbose=True)

In [104]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue8.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue8.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)

In [107]:
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()

color = 'tab:red'
ax1.set_xlabel('Epoch')
ax1.set_ylabel('Total Loss (classifier + TD-VAE)', color=color)
ax1.plot(log.index, log['tloss'], color=color)
ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color)

ax2 = ax1.twinx()  # instantiate a second axes that shares the same x-axis

color = 'tab:blue'
ax2.set_ylabel('Validation Accuracy (classifier)', color=color)  # we already handled the x-label with ax1
ax2.plot(log.index, log['val_acc'], color=color)
ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color)

fig.tight_layout()  # otherwise the right y-label is slightly clipped
plt.show()

with open("./Data/genesys_mouse_embryo_11_clusters_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_data.pkl", 'rb') as file_handle:
    data = pickle.load(file_handle)

dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_test'], data['y_test'])
loader = DataLoader(dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
train_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_train'], data['y_train'])
train_loader = DataLoader(train_dataset,
                         batch_size = batch_size,
                         shuffle = True, drop_last=True)
val_dataset = Mouse_Dataset(data['X_val'], data['y_val'])

In [115]:
#logger = {'tloss': [], 'val_acc': []}
#best_val_acc = 0.99
best_loss = min(logger['tloss'])
for epoch in range(n_epochs):
    h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    c, s = 0, 0
    pBar = tqdm(train_loader)
    model.train()
    for sample in pBar:
        h = tuple([each.data for each in h])
        x = sample['x'].to(device)
        y = sample['y'].to(device)
        optimizer.zero_grad()
        t = np.random.choice(time_bins-1)
        p, h = model.predict(x, h, t)
        model.get_belief(x, h)
        tdvae_loss = model.calculate_loss(t)
        nll_loss = criterion(p, y)
        loss = tdvae_loss + nll_loss
        # print(loss)
        s = ((s*c)+(float(loss.item())*len(p)))/(c+len(p))
        c += len(p)
        pBar.set_description('Epoch {} Train: '.format(epoch) +str(round(float(s),4)))
        wl = np.random.choice(2)
        if wl == 0 :
            tdvae_loss.backward()
        else :
            nll_loss.backward()
        #loss.backward()
        nn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), clip)
        optimizer.step()
    logger['tloss'].append(s)
    sch.step(s)

    val_h = model.init_hidden(batch_size)
    model.eval()
    y_pred, y_true = [], []
    with torch.no_grad():
        for sample in val_loader:
            val_h = tuple([each.data for each in val_h])
            x = sample['x'].to(device)
            y = sample['y'].to(device)
            #t = np.random.choice(11)
            t=1
            p, val_h = model.predict_proba(x, val_h, t)
            y_pred.append(p.cpu().detach().numpy())
            y_true.append(y.cpu().detach().numpy())
    y_pred = np.concatenate(y_pred)
    y_true = np.concatenate(y_true)

    val_acc = (y_true == y_pred.argmax(axis=1)).mean()
    logger['val_acc'].append(val_acc)
    print("Validation Accuracy {:.4f}".format(val_acc))
    if (val_acc >= 0.99) & (s < best_loss):
        # print('Model improved')
        #best_val_acc = val_acc
        best_loss = s
        print(best_loss)
        torch.save(model.state_dict(), path+"/genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue9.pth")
        val_stats = {'pred': y_pred, 'true': y_true}

with open('log_genesys_model_trained_on_mouse_embryo_500_cells_per_state_2500_GPC_UPC_20240302_continue9.pkl', 'wb') as f:
    pickle.dump(logger, f)

In [118]:
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()

color = 'tab:red'
ax1.set_xlabel('Epoch')
ax1.set_ylabel('Total Loss (classifier + TD-VAE)', color=color)
ax1.plot(log.index, log['tloss'], color=color)
ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color)

ax2 = ax1.twinx()  # instantiate a second axes that shares the same x-axis

color = 'tab:blue'
ax2.set_ylabel('Validation Accuracy (classifier)', color=color)  # we already handled the x-label with ax1
ax2.plot(log.index, log['val_acc'], color=color)
ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor=color)

fig.tight_layout()  # otherwise the right y-label is slightly clipped
plt.show()
